    {
      "id": "3100773bc4f3756e8eb5261c93dadc3f394f2a5a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-28 21:27:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThis will fix the build/usage problem, but it means that RHEL6 will not be able to test recovery problems, even with a patched kernel.  Adding the workaround described in LU-9698 would allow us to continue testing with patched kernels (which is most of the RHEL6 server kernels).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
